Types

Graph[T] = object
  adjList*: Table[T, HashSet[T]]
An undirected graph with a generic node type. Adjacency lists are stored as a hash table of hash sets, that way checking if a node is in a graph is fast. Neighbor nodes' order doesn't matter and removing/adding edges should be fast so neigbors are stored as a hash set. 
Point2D = tuple[x, y: float]
Point2DInt = tuple[x, y: int]
PointGraph = Graph[Point2D]
